      "date": "2011-11-11 18:46:11.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\nPatch itself looks OK.\n\nThe test looks good as well, but I think we would get much more stressful testing by having the lustre/tests/racer.sh script always try to run racer in every mountpoint on the client.  Something like:\n\nRACERDIRS=${RACERDIRS:-\"$DIR1 $DIR2\"}\n\nSince that is not strictly related to this bugfix, it could be landed as a follow-on patch.",
